1 (i) One or more citations for a payable violation issued under §
2 26–201 of the Transportation Article; [or]
3 (ii) One or more fines imposed at a hearing or trial by the court; OR
4 (III) ONE OR MORE CIVIL CITATIONS ISSUED UNDER AN
5 AUTOMATED TRAFFIC ENFORCEMENT PROGRAM.
6 (2) A defendant who agrees to enter into an installment plan agreement for
7 the payment of one or more citations OR CIVIL CITATIONS under paragraph [(1)(i)] (1) of
8 this subsection consents to conviction OR CIVIL LIABILITY, AS APPROPRIATE, at the time
9 of the agreement.
10 (c) (1) A defendant who is sentenced to pay one or more fines OR CIVIL
11 PENALTIES that total at least $150 and certifies that the defendant is unable to pay the
12 fine [or], fines, CIVIL PENALTY, OR CIVIL PENALTIES may apply to the clerk of the court
13 to make installment payments in accordance with this section.
14 (2) An installment plan agreement under this section shall:
15 (i) Require that the defendant make installment payments on the
16 total amount of the fine [or], fines, CIVIL PENALTY, OR CIVIL PENALTIES covered by the
17 agreement; and
18 (ii) Specify the offenses and citations to which the agreement
19 applies.
20 (3) As a condition of an installment plan agreement, a defendant who
21 enters into the agreement shall inform the clerk of the court of any change of address during
22 the term of the agreement.
23 (4) (i) If a defendant fails to pay a fine OR CIVIL PENALTY in
24 accordance with an installment plan agreement under this section, the clerk of the court
25 may:
26 1. Refer the amount of the unpaid outstanding fine OR CIVIL
27 PENALTY to the Central Collection Unit of the Department of Budget and Management; or
28 2. Process the unpaid outstanding fine OR CIVIL PENALTY
29 as it would other outstanding fines OR CIVIL PENALTIES owed the court.
30 (ii) The clerk of the court shall provide notice to the defendant of the
31 disposition of the unpaid outstanding fine OR CIVIL PENALTY under subparagraph (i) of
32 this paragraph in the same manner required for other outstanding fines OR CIVIL
33 PENALTIES processed in the same manner.

